1337
01:13:01,800 --> 01:13:05,300
But actually let me tell you how this, how we got here.

1338
01:13:05,300 --> 01:13:06,800
see what happened is,

1339
01:13:06,800 --> 01:13:09,400
15 years ago, if you wanted to use a computer,

1340
01:13:09,400 --> 01:13:13,400
the only way you could do it was to, was with proprietary software,

1341
01:13:14,300 --> 01:13:17,000
software that divides and subjugates the users.

1342
01:13:17,000 --> 01:13:18,900
And most people just...

1343
01:13:18,900 --> 01:13:20,200
A lot of people didn't like it.

1344
01:13:20,200 --> 01:13:21,700
But they saw no alternative.

1345
01:13:21,700 --> 01:13:25,500
But some of us were determined to make an alternative.

1346
01:13:25,500 --> 01:13:29,500
And we said we're gonna develop a free operating system,

1347
01:13:29,600 --> 01:13:31,400
a free software operating system

1348
01:13:31,400 --> 01:13:37,100
that will give users the chance to have freedom while they use their computers.

1349
01:13:37,700 --> 01:13:40,300
Now a lot of people said, "Well, it's a nice idea

1350
01:13:40,300 --> 01:13:42,600
but it's so hard, you'll never get it done,

1351
01:13:42,600 --> 01:13:46,500
so I don't wanna participate, I don't believe you can ever get it done."

1352
01:13:46,500 --> 01:13:49,300
But luckily not everybody said that.

1353
01:13:49,300 --> 01:13:53,200
And clearly, we knew we would eventually get the kernel done.

1354
01:13:53,200 --> 01:13:54,500
But as it happens.

1355
01:13:54,500 --> 01:13:57,600
somebody else did a better kernel before we did.

1356
01:13:57,600 --> 01:14:01,200
Now in the old days, we had an overall strategy

1357
01:14:01,200 --> 01:14:04,800
from calling people's attention to the importance of freedom

1358
01:14:04,800 --> 01:14:08,800
To the freedom they can have, or not have, when they use a computer.

1359
01:14:09,500 --> 01:14:11,600
Well what can we do about it? As far as I can tell,

1360
01:14:11,600 --> 01:14:17,600
the only workable way of trying to change this make that strategy work again

1361
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:23,800
is to, spread the word that the operating system you're using is actually the GNU system.

1362
01:14:23,900 --> 01:14:26,100
Somewhat modified of course.

1363
01:14:27,200 --> 01:14:29,100
And when people know this,

1364
01:14:29,100 --> 01:14:32,600
they'll take a look at the reasons we developed this system.

1365
01:14:32,600 --> 01:14:34,500
They'll think about these issues.

1366
01:14:34,500 --> 01:14:37,300
And some of them will decide they agree.

1367
01:14:37,300 --> 01:14:40,600
So I ask people, please tell the people this is the GNU system.

1368
01:14:40,600 --> 01:14:44,600
It's the combination of GNU and Linux so we can call it GNU/Linux

